  "body": "I have some Issues when im trying to use viaIr \r\nThe version I'm working on : hardhat@2.12.8-viair.0\r\nmy hardhat.config.js\r\n```require(\"@nomicfoundation/hardhat-toolbox\");\r\n\r\n/** @type import('hardhat/config').HardhatUserConfig */\r\nmodule.exports = {\r\n  solidity: \"0.8.17\",\r\n  optimizer: {\r\n    enabled: true,\r\n    runs: 1000,\r\n  },\r\n  viaIR: true,\r\n};\r\n```\r\n\r\nthe error i got\r\n```\r\n CompilerError: Stack too deep. Try compiling with `--via-ir` (cli) or the equivalent `viaIR: true` (standard JSON) while enabling the optimizer. Otherwise, try removing local variables.\r\n  --> contracts/xxx.sol:63:13:\r\n   |\r\n63 |             param[14],\r\n   |             ^^^^^\r\n\r\n\r\nError HH600: Compilation failed\r\n```\r\n\r\nIs there a specific way or special settings in order to work on it ?",
